The paper discusses strategies to improve neural network-based predictive methods for MOOC student course trajectory modeling, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also applies ideas from NLP (Natural Language Processing), which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses regularization techniques, which could place it under cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
